Class jdbcpostgreSQL

java.lang.Object
jdbcpostgreSQL
public class jdbcpostgreSQL extends Object
This class's main purpose is to be utilized by the manager home page to execute specific queries to view the inventory and sales report from the database.

  • Constructor Details

    • jdbcpostgreSQL

      jdbcpostgreSQL(String table, String inventory_item, String start, String end, String entree, String protein, String side)
      This constructor is used for the manager home page's queries. It mainly uses select statements to access specific values from the database.
      Parameters:
      table - the name of table that will be queried
      inventory_item - the type of item to be selected in the table (protein, side, topping, etc.)
      start - the beginning date to start the query
      end - the end date to end the query time interval
      entree - the entree that is selected from the list (bowl, taco, burrito, etc.)
      protein - the protein option that is ordered (chicken, steak, beef, etc.)
      side - the side that is ordered with the entree (chips, salsa, guac, etc.)

    • jdbcpostgreSQL

      jdbcpostgreSQL(String table, String quantityAmt, String sufficientSupplyValue, String itemID)
      This constructor is used for the update function of the manager home page. The constructor uses the UPDATE clause to create a statement that modifies the database's quantity and sufficient supply.
      Parameters:
      table - the table within the database to be queried from
      quantityAmt - the new quantity of the item that you want to change
      sufficientSupplyValue - the value for whether or not the item has a sufficient supply (0 or 1)
      itemID - the ID of the item that you want to modify

    • jdbcpostgreSQL

      jdbcpostgreSQL(String inventoryFunction)
      This constructor is used for the Restock Report and Update Inventory Supply
      Parameters:
      inventoryFunction - function to be executed on Inventory table
